Definition: the quality of being magnificent or splendid or grand
Example: for magnificence and personal service there is the Queen's hotel; his `Hamlet' lacks the brilliance that one expects; it is the university that gives the scene its stately splendor; an imaginative mix of old-fashioned grandeur and colorful art; advertisers capitalize on the grandness and elegance it brings to their products
Synonyms: adj, all, impressive, magnificent, brilliance, superior, brilliant, splendor, splendour, grandeur, grandness, noble, grand, extraordinary, dignified, elegance, the, quality, of, being, or, splendid, for, and, personal, service, there, is, Queen, s, hotel, his, Hamlet, lacks, that, one, expects, it, university, gives, scene, its, stately, an, imaginative, mix, old-fashioned, colorful, art, advertisers, capitalize, on, brings, to, their, products
Category: noun.attribute
